Standard Chartered Ghana Falls Most in 9 Months as Profit Slows

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-04-29T13:19:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/standard-chartered-ghana-falls-most-in-9-months-as-profit-slows.html
Standard Chartered Plc’s unit in
 Ghana  fell the most in more than nine months after saying first-
quarter profit declined 37 percent.  Standard Chartered Bank Ghana Ltd. dropped 3.25 cedis, or
5.4 percent, to 56.75 cedis by 1 p.m. in Accra, the capital.
That was the most since July 8, 2010.  The bank’s profit slid to 14 million cedis ($9.3 million)
in the three months through March, from 22 million cedis a year
earlier, it said in a statement published in Accra-based Daily
Graphic newspaper today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 